## How This Project Works

This project uses [FORGE](https://github.com/bwcarty/forge-public) (Framework for Organized Reliable Gated Engineering) for spec-driven, evidence-gated development.

**Two hard rules:**
1. Every change has a matching spec
2. Every session ends with a session log

### Specs as Context Anchors

Specs are more than task descriptions — they are **context anchors** that persist decision context across AI sessions, team changes, and time. When a new session begins, the spec carries forward the *why* behind each decision, not just the *what*. This means context survives session boundaries instead of being lost and rediscovered. Martin Fowler's writing on context anchoring (2026) validated this pattern, though FORGE has practiced it from the start: every spec is a living document that prevents context loss in AI-assisted workflows.

